<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
Mesosoma (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Sphecodes tibeticus Astafurova &amp; Niu, sp. nov., holotype, male (A, C-E), and S. laticaudatus Tsuneki, male (B) A, B head, frontal view C antenna, lateral view D mesosoma, dorsal view E metasoma, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.79.57276.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469620" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">5D</figureCitation>
) black, tarsi brownish. Wings hyaline with brown stigma and veins; hind wing with the angle between basal (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">M</emphasis>
) and cubital (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Cu</emphasis>
) veins 80Â°, costal margin with six hamuli. Pronotum, between dorsal and lateral surfaces, with sharp angle. Mesoscutum mostly with confluent punctures ca. 20-30 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Î¼m">Î¼m</normalizedToken>
. Mesoscutellum, hypoepimeral area, mesepisternum, propodeal triangle and lateral part of propodeum roughly reticulate-rugose.
</paragraph>
