<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
Metasoma dark black (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Sphecodes tibeticus Astafurova &amp; Niu, sp. nov., holotype, male (A, C-E), and S. laticaudatus Tsuneki, male (B) A, B head, frontal view C antenna, lateral view D mesosoma, dorsal view E metasoma, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.79.57276.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469620" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">5E</figureCitation>
); terga scarcely punctate, T1 almost impunctate with a few microscopic punctures, remaining terga with a few shallow punctures on anterior half, marginal zones impunctate, smooth (except finely tessellate on T4); sterna delicately tessellate with numerous microscopical setae pores; gonocoxite dorsally with impression; gonostylus with semi-oval membranous part (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Sphecodes tibeticus Astafurova &amp; Niu, sp. nov., holotype, male A habitus, lateral view B labels C, D genitalia, dorsal view (C), lateral view (D). Scale bars: 1.0 mm (A), 0.5 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.79.57276.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469619" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">4C, D</figureCitation>
